Queens Park Rangers captain  Joey Barton  was banned for 12 games for incidents surrounding his red
card at Manchester City on the last day of the Premier League
soccer season, Sky Sports reported.  The Football Association held a disciplinary hearing that
Barton attended today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
